        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 5:11PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 510 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Arden. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central Tom
Green and northeastern Irion Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
